References A set of questions on the consumption of dark green vegetables and dried beans or peas that was asked in the DBQ section for 2001-2002 was not continued in this section for 2003-2004. A new question (DBD229) was added to the NHANES 2001-2002 questionnaire to determine whether the respondent received free or reduced price meal at the summer program. Only youth 4-19 years old who reported receiving free or reduced meals in school were asked this question. Analysts need to be aware of this specific skip pattern for this question.
